A vintage 1950s scientific illustration style depicting a single glowing geometric crystal or gem with multiple faceted surfaces, each facet reflecting a different scene: one shows organized file folders, another displays flowing data streams, another reveals mechanical gears working in harmony, and another shows a searchlight beam. The crystal floats against a deep navy blue backdrop with subtle atomic-age starburst patterns. Warm amber and cool teal tones contrast throughout. The crystal appears solid yet mysteriously versatile, suggesting hidden depths and multiple purposes within one elegant form. Rendered with the crosshatching and limited color palette typical of mid-century technical manuals and educational posters.
